<!-- Button trigger modal -->
<button type="button" class="btn mr-1 px-2 py-1" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#mapStationsModal">
<i class="bi bi-question-circle"></i>
</button>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal" id="mapStationsModal" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h1 class="modal-title fs-5">Map stations always visible on map</h1>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>If enabled, the map station for the current area will always be visible as a special tile on the map even before you have reached it.
        This affects both the pause menu map and the HUD mini-map.</p>
        <p>In general, disabling this option will greatly increase the amount of exploration needed to beat the game.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
